<collectionCode id="819D979A35060D365A87894A447BFAB4" box="[1258,1347,1310,1336]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15506" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15506" name="Universidade Estadual de Feira de Santana" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" type="Herbarium">HUEFS</collectionCode>
253745, 
<collectionCode id="819D979A35060D365EE5891641D9FAD0" box="[136,225,1346,1372]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15506" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15506" name="Universidade Estadual de Feira de Santana" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" type="Herbarium">HUEFS</collectionCode>
253766
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E7330F5F35060D365ED089324494FA28" blockId="4.[136,1452,1274,1769]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35060D365ED089324021FA0C" bold="true" box="[189,281,1382,1408]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Habitat</emphasis>
:—This species was found associated with periphyton of 
<taxonomicName id="208C74DC35060D365DEA8932456FFA0C" box="[903,1111,1382,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lentibulariaceae" genus="Utricularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliosa">
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35060D365DEA8932456FFA0C" box="[903,1111,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Utricularia foliosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="208C74DC35060D365AE489324444FA0C" authorityName="A. Gray" authorityYear="1837" box="[1161,1404,1382,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cabombaceae" genus="Cabomba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Nymphaeales" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caroliniana">
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35060D365AE489324444FA0C" box="[1161,1404,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Cabomba caroliniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. EC 0.02 (± 0.01 mS 
<superScript id="10F9A21735060D365F2F89DF4049FA14" attach="left" box="[322,369,1418,1445]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">cm-1</superScript>
), 
<collectionCode id="819D979A35060D365FE589DE4088FA28" box="[392,432,1418,1444]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14073" name="Société d'Agriculture Sciences et Arts" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" type="Herbarium">DO</collectionCode>
6.3 (± 
<quantity id="2074A2BA35060D365F9289DE4375FA29" box="[511,589,1418,1445]" metricMagnitude="-7" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" unit="mg" value="0.3">0.3 mg</quantity>
L- 
<superScript id="10F9A21735060D365C0789DE4349FA14" attach="right" box="[618,625,1418,1432]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">1</superScript>
), pH 7.5 (± 0.8), TDS 0.01 (± 0.005), 
<collectionCode id="819D979A35060D365A7489DF4512FA29" box="[1049,1066,1419,1445]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">T</collectionCode>
29.8 (± 1.8 ºC), WT 0.6 (± 
<quantity id="2074A2BA35060D365B3689DE449CFA28" box="[1371,1444,1418,1444]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7999999999999998" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" unit="m" value="0.18">0.18m</quantity>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E7330F5F35060D365ED089FA424AF964" blockId="4.[136,1452,1274,1769]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35060D365ED089FA41CDFA44" bold="true" box="[189,245,1454,1480]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Note</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="208C74DC35060D365F7489FB4326FA44" box="[281,542,1455,1481]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Cosmarium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="pygmaeum">
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35060D365F7489FB4326FA44" box="[281,542,1455,1481]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Cosmarium pygmaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species with cosmopolitan distribution, with a bunch of records mainly in Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="831D72AE35060D365E84898640E2FA60" author="Guiry, M. D. &amp; Guiry, G. M." box="[233,474,1490,1516]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" refId="ref4867" refString="Guiry, M. D. &amp; Guiry, G. M. (2020) AlgaeBase. World-wide electronic publication, National University of Ireland, Galway. Available from: http: // www. algaebase. org (accessed 19 December 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Guiry &amp; Guiry 2020</bibRefCitation>
). However, in 
<collectingCountry id="9F9B4FCF35060D365CEF898643FEFA60" box="[642,710,1490,1516]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and even in South America, this species is rarely reported in the literature. There is only a record of its occurrence in the Brazilian territory, which was based on the sample gathered in municipality of Rio Claro, State of 
<collectingRegion id="2548C1BD35060D365C538A4E4389F9B8" box="[574,689,1562,1588]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
(Bicudo 1969, 
<bibRefCitation id="831D72AE35060D365D088A4E4507F9B8" author="Bicudo, C. E. M. &amp; Araujo, A. &amp; Biolo, S." box="[869,1087,1562,1588]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" refId="ref4481" refString="Bicudo, C. E. M., Araujo, A. &amp; Biolo, S. (2019) Flora Ficologica do Estado de Sao Paulo. Parte 3: Zygnematophyceae 1. ed. Vol. 4. RiMa Editora, Sao Paulo, pp. 1 - 309." type="book" year="2019">
Bicudo 
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35060D365DD28A4F42C1F9B8" box="[959,1017,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, the material from 
<collectingRegion id="2548C1BD35060D365B078A4E4493F9B8" box="[1386,1451,1562,1588]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Bahia</collectingRegion>
represents the second record of that species in 
<collectingCountry id="9F9B4FCF35060D365CEE8A6A43F3F9D4" box="[643,715,1598,1624]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Overall, it is one of the most polymorphic and smaller 
<taxonomicName id="208C74DC35060D365B448A6B4494F9D5" authorityName="Corda ex Ralfs" authorityYear="1848" box="[1321,1452,1599,1625]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Cosmarium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" phylum="Charophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5F8D34D35060D365B448A6B4494F9D5" box="[1321,1452,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Cosmarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxa occurring in the Marimbus. The main morphological variations in the specimens from 
<collectingRegion id="2548C1BD35060D365AFD8A3645E9F9F0" box="[1168,1233,1634,1660]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Bahia</collectingRegion>
are the sinus, from open to closed, the central granule which can be next to the apical margin or close to the isthmus, and the papillae at the basal angles, which could be more or less projected (
<figureCitation id="7FB713DA35060D365CA38AFE4229F949" box="[718,785,1706,1733]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[136,243,2002,2024]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,278,1974]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[178,1409,278,1974]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Line drawings. 1. Cosmarium boeckii var.areolatum 2. C. clepsydra var. incrassatum 3. C. heptangulare 4. C. kanetsunae 5. C. pygmaeum 6. C. trinodulum 7. C. trinodulum var. brasiliense 8. C. trinodulum var. pilgeri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5420998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5420998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="831D72AE35060D365DD68AFF4557F948" author="Kouwets, F. A. C." box="[955,1135,1706,1733]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" pagination="193 - 263" refId="ref5012" refString="Kouwets, F. A. C. (1987) Desmids from the Auvergne (France). Hydrobiologia 146: 193 - 263. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00016347" type="journal article" year="1987">Kouwets (1987)</bibRefCitation>
the arrangement of granules on the cell wall is very variable, and without any taxonomic value.
</paragraph>
